{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place cardamom, garlic and chilli into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>.","Add flour, ghee, oil, salt and water and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>, then knead <nobr>2 min\/<\/nobr>.","Transfer onto a silicone bread mat or floured work surface and shape into a ball. Transfer into a bowl, cover with a damp tea towel and allow to rest for 30 minutes.","Transfer dough onto silicone bread mat or lightly floured work surface. Divide dough into 12 equal portions (approx. 70 g each) and cover with a damp tea towel. Using a rolling pin, roll each ball into a circle (approx. 18 cm), then cover with a damp tea towel.","Place a large non-stick frying pan over high heat. Brush both sides of the parathas with oil. Working 1 at a time, fry parathas for 1 minute on each side until evenly browned. Lift paratha and drizzle a few drops of oil into frying pan. Continue frying for a few seconds on each side until they start to look a little flaky. Transfer onto a plate and brush with ghee (optional). Cover to keep warm until ready to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1 tsp ground cardamom","1 garlic clove","1 - 2 fresh long green chillies, trimmed  and cut into halves (optional)","500 g wholemeal flour (see Tips), plus extra for rolling","50 g ghee (see Tips), plus extra for brushing","15 g olive oil, plus extra for brushing","1 tsp salt","220 g hot water"]}],"id":"r132080","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-XJBzs6O_GnI\/XZaoYuv-lOI\/AAAAAAAAhJs\/w8yxA5tTezk1ScmCJbFHdnDq8h6eed2DgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_niNlqMpI-YF6m5Tx.png","title":"Parathas","publishedAt":"2017-07-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4.9 g","fat":"5.5 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"27.2 g","calories":"792 kJ \/ 188 kcal"},"usefulItems":"silicone bread mat, tea towel, bowl, rolling pin, 1 plate, large non-stick frying pan, pastry brush, stove top","hintsAndTricks":["For a more authentic paratha, you can replace wholemeal flour with atta flour (available at Indian grocers or online). Alternatively, you can replace the wholemeal flour with plain flour.","Parathas are an unleavened bread (similar to naan) and often served with curries or potato-based dishes."],"basicInfo":["easy","40m","1h 30m","12 portions"]}